name: Filipino Spring Rolls
author: Belinda Jean
summary: I like to dip these in spicy vinegar with garlic.
ingredients: 3 large carrots, cut into thin strips
1 pinch salt and ground black pepper to taste
2 cups oil for frying, or as needed
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons vegetable oil in a wok or large saucepan over medium heat
Add onion and garlic; cook and stir until softened, about 5 minutes
Stir in ground chicken; cook until no longer pink, about 5 minutes
Mix cabbage, bean sprouts, and carrots into the chicken mixture
Place 1 spoonful of chicken mixture in the center of 1 spring roll wrapper
Fold in opposing edges and roll up wrapper
Repeat with remaining chicken mixture and spring roll wrappers
Heat 2 cups oil in a wok or large saucepan over medium heat
Fry spring rolls in batches until golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes per batch
